Class Track

  • java.lang.Object
    • SuperTrack
      • Track

  • public class Track
extends SuperTrack

    This class extends the class SuperTrack. By doing this this class can make use of all the properties inherited and can be set in the constructor of this class.

    This class is still a basic track so it does not have any other additional properties. However the method toString is being overridden to change it's functionality and output only what it needs to output.

    Author:
    Alexander Chetcuti

        This constructor initialises an object of type track, and sets all the required data in their appropriate fields.

        Parameters:
        title - The title of the track.
        artist - The artist of the track.
        released - The date released of the track
        length - The length in seconds of the track.
        rating - The rating from 0 to 5 of the track.
        size - The size in KiloBytes of the track.
        guest - The guest artist of the track.
        countPlayed - The count played for this track.
        album - The album of this track.

    • Method Detail

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()

        This method overrides the method toString and outputs only the necessary information. First we create a simple date format for the date to be converted to a proper string. Then a calculation for the amount of minuted and seconds in done on the property length. The method then return a concatenated string of the most important information found in this class.

        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        The final concatenated string.
